                 To specify declarations about the party associated with
                 the cover, such as 'Party is main Driver under this
                 cover?', 'Party Is Excluded from this cover?'.

02030            REL, Relationship
                 To specify the relationship that this party has with the
                 proposer.


02040         Segment group 31: EVE-GEI-ATT-DTM-MOA-PCD-QRS-QTY-RFF-PCC-
                                LOC-FTX-SG32
              A group that provides the history details for claims against
              one insurance cover.

02050            EVE, Event
                 To identify one claim that has been made against the
                 insurance cover.

02060            GEI, Processing information
                 Contains a coded indication of how the claim is to be
                 processed if the message is being used to update a policy,
                 such as 'Added', 'Deleted' or 'Changed'.

02070            ATT, Attribute
                 Contains coded attributed relating to the claim, such as
                 'Cause Code', 'Consequence Code'.

02080            DTM, Date/time/period
                 To specify dates related to the date, such as 'Incident
                 Date', 'Claim Date'.

02090            MOA, Monetary amount
                 To specify monetary amounts relating to the claim, such as
                 'Claim Value', 'Amount Paid'.

02100            PCD, Percentage details
                 To specify percentages related to the claim, such as
                 'Percentage of Responsibility'.

02110            QRS, Query and response
                 To specify declarations about the claim, such as
                 'Bonus/Malus Affected?', 'Claim Fully Settled?'.

02120            QTY, Quantity
                 To specify quantities relating to the claim.

02130            RFF, Reference
                 To provide references relating to the claim, such as
                 'Claim Number'.

02140            PCC, Premium calculation component details
                 To specify premium components that this claim gave rise
                 to.

02150            LOC, Place/location identification
                 To specify the location of the incident.

02160            FTX, Free text
                 To provide additional text information about the claim.


02170            Segment group 32: PNA-ADR-RFF-CTA-COM
                 To provide information about the holding insurer and
                 broker at the time of the claim.

02180               PNA, Party identification
                    To identify one party for the claim, such as broker and
                    insurer.

02190               ADR, Address
                    To provide the address for the party associated with
                    the claim.

02200               RFF, Reference
                    To specify references for the party and the claim.

02210               CTA, Contact information
                    To specify a contact at the party who handles the
                    claim.

02220               COM, Communication contact
                    To provide communication numbers for the claim party.

02230   UNS, Section control
        A mandatory service segment placed before the first user segment in
        the detail section to avoid segment collision.


02240   Segment group 33: DTM-RFF-QRS-FTX-SG34-SG35-SG37
        A group that provides details of previous fleet claims experience.
        This section is only used for commercial fleet insurance.

02250      DTM, Date/time/period
           To specify the duration of one period of fleet experience.

02260      RFF, Reference
           To specify references related to the fleet experience, such as
           'Insurer's Policy Number', 'Broker's Risk Reference'.

02270      QRS, Query and response
           To specify declarations for the fleet experience, such as 'Is
           claims history confirmed?', 'Is foreign use included?'.

02280      FTX, Free text
           To provide text details of why the claims history is unconfirmed
           (if appropriate).


02290      Segment group 34: PNA-ADR-CTA-COM
           To provide details for the holding insurer and broker at the
           time of the fleet experience.

02300         PNA, Party identification
              To identify one party relating to the fleet experience, such
              as insurer and broker.

02310         ADR, Address
              To provide address details for the party.

02320         CTA, Contact information
              To provide a contact name for the party that handles the
              fleet experience.

02330         COM, Communication contact
              To provide communication numbers for the party.


02340      Segment group 35: GEI-DTM-QTY-MOA-SG36
           A group that provides a breakdown of figures for the fleet
           experience.

02350         GEI, Processing information
              Coded indication of whether the breakdown figures should be
              processed as being the same as at the date of the previous
              fleet experience or as being updated.

02360         DTM, Date/time/period
              To specify dates relating to the fleet experience, such as
              'Calculated To Date', 'Event Date of Last Claim Included'.

02370         QTY, Quantity
              To specify quantities relating to the fleet experience, such
              as 'Total Claims Reported', 'Claims Reported Outstanding
              Number'.

02380         MOA, Monetary amount
              To specify monetary amounts relating to the fleet experience,
              such as 'Claims Paid and Outstanding Cost', 'Claims
              Outstanding Cost'.


02390         Segment group 36: ICD-ATT-MOA-QTY-FTX
              To provide a breakdown by cover for the fleet experience
              figures.

02400            ICD, Insurance cover description
                 To identify one type of insurance cover.

02410            ATT, Attribute
                 To specify coded attributes relating to the fleet
                 experience cover breakdown, such as 'Type of Excess
                 Applying', 'Excess Application Code'.

02420            MOA, Monetary amount
                 To specify monetary amounts relating to the cover
                 breakdown, such as 'Excess Value', 'Claims Cost Paid'.

02430            QTY, Quantity
                 To specify quantities relating to the cover breakdown,
                 such as 'Number of Claims', 'Number of Claims
                 Outstanding'.

02440            FTX, Free text
                 To provide additional description of the cover.


02450      Segment group 37: EVE-GEI-ATT-DTM-ICD-MOA-RFF-QRS-FTX
           To specify individual claim details that occurred during the
           fleet experience.

02460         EVE, Event
              To identify one claim.

02470         GEI, Processing information
              Coded indication of how this claim is to be processed if the
              message is being used to update a policy.

02480         ATT, Attribute
              Coded attributes relating to the claim, such as 'Cause Code',
              'Consequence Code'.

02490         DTM, Date/time/period
              To specify dates relating to the claim, such as 'Incident
              Date', 'Claim Date'.

02500         ICD, Insurance cover description
              To specify the cover against which this claim was made.

02510         MOA, Monetary amount
              To specify monetary amounts relating to the claim, such as
              'Claim Value', 'Paid Amount'.

02520         RFF, Reference
              To specify references for the claim, such as 'Insurer Claim
              Number', 'Broker Claim Reference'.

02530         QRS, Query and response
              To specify declarations about the claim, such as 'Bonus/Malus
              Affected?'.

02540         FTX, Free text
              To provide additional text details about the claim.

02550   UNT, Message trailer
        A service segment ending a message, giving the total number of
        segments in the message (including the UNH & UNT) and the control
        reference number of the message.

